com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations

Class SequenceExtractionUtilities

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.SequenceExtractionUtilities

  • public class SequenceExtractionUtilities
extends Object
    Provides methods for extracting a portion of a sequence to a new sequence document. Also provides methods for reverse complementing and translation.

    Although this class will accept any SequenceDocument as input, the extracted region may not include all information that was present on some SequenceDocument sub-classes. For example MolecularStructureDocument information will not be included in extracted regions. The following information will be included in extracted regions:

    • Nucleotides / amino acids returned from SequenceDocument.getCharSequence()
    • SequenceAnnotations
    • DocumentFields
    • NucleotideGraphs
    See Also:
    SequenceUtilities

    • Method Detail

      • getReversedSequenceName

        public static String getReversedSequenceName(String sequenceName)
        Appends the " (reversed)" suffix to the sequence name (or removes if it is already there). For example:
        getReversedSequenceName("test") returns "test (reversed)"
        getReversedSequenceName("test (reversed)") returns "test"
        Parameters:
        sequenceName - the sequence index to change the name of.
        Returns:
        sequenceName with " (reversed)" appended (or removed if it was already there)

      • getComplementWithoutReverseSequenceName

        public static String getComplementWithoutReverseSequenceName(String sequenceName)
        Appends the " (complement without reverse)" suffix to the sequence name (or removes if it is already there). Also takes into account existing " (reversed") suffix and uses " (reverse without complement)" instead.
        Parameters:
        sequenceName - the sequence index to change the name of.
        Returns:
        sequenceName with " (complement without reverse)" appended (or removed if it was already there)
        Since:
        API 4.600 (Geneious 6.0.0)

      • removeGaps

        public static SequenceDocument removeGaps(SequenceDocument sequence,
                          boolean mustGeneratedDefaultSequenceDocument)
        creates a sequence the same as the given sequence but with gap characters removed. All internal information such as annotations are adjusted accordingly.
        Parameters:
        sequence - the sequence to remove gaps from
        mustGeneratedDefaultSequenceDocument - true to ensure the returned sequence will be an instance of a DefaultSequenceDocument. If this is false, the returned sequence may be any SequenceDocument implementation.
        Returns:
        a sequence without gaps
        Since:
        API 4.14 (Geneious 5.1)

        Parameters:

      • reverseComplement

        public static DefaultNucleotideSequence reverseComplement(SequenceDocument sequenceToReverse,
                                          boolean appendReversedToName,
                                          boolean includeOriginalBaseNumbersAnnotation)
        Create a sequence that is the reverse complement another sequence.
        Parameters:
        sequenceToReverse - the sequence to create the reverse complement of.
        appendReversedToName - true to append " (reversed)" to the name of sequenceToReverse to form the name of the returned sequence. false to give the returned sequence the same name as sequenceToReverse.
        includeOriginalBaseNumbersAnnotation - true to include an annotation (which is invisible to end users) indicating the original numbering of this sequence. false to exclude it. Usually this should be true, except in cases where we are dealing with enormous amounts of data (e.g. next gen sequencing) in which case we want to exclude it for performance reasons.
        Returns:
        the reverse complement of sequenceToReverse
        Since:
        API 4.11 (Geneious 5.0)

        Copy all document fields (such as organism, taxonomy and common name) from any SequenceDocument to a DefaultSequenceDocument. This should only be called on documents that are identical apart from gaps since some fields (for example accession) would be incorrect on a modified/partial instance of the document.

      • extractIntervals

        @Deprecated
public static DefaultSequenceDocument extractIntervals(SequenceDocument sourceDocument,
                                                  String overrideName,
                                                  GeneticCode geneticCode,
                                                  int translationFrame,
                                                  boolean residuesOnly,
                                                  List<SequenceAnnotationInterval> intervals,
                                                  boolean allowReverseComplement,
                                                  boolean removeGaps)
        Deprecated. use extractIntervals(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence.SequenceDocument, com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions) instead.
        Extracts a group of intervals to a new sequence document
        Parameters:
        sourceDocument - To extract from
        geneticCode - translates from nucleotide's to amino acids if specified, or performs no translation if this parameter is null
        translationFrame - offset for each interval (typically 0, 1 or 2 for DNA). If not translating, this should be 0.
        residuesOnly - whether to extract only residues or to include the annotations.
        intervals - to extract
        allowReverseComplement - if false, automatic reverse complementing will not happen. If true, intervals of the form (from, to) where from >= to will be reverse complemented.
        overrideName - name of new sequence. If not given will be derived from seqeunce name and type of extraction
        removeGaps - if true remove any gaps
        Returns:
        the newly generated sequence document.

      • extractOrThrow

        public static SequenceDocument extractOrThrow(SequenceDocument sourceDocument,
                              SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions extractionOptions)
                                       throws DocumentOperationException
        Extracts one or more intervals from a sequence as a new sequence document. This differs from extractIntervals(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence.SequenceDocument, com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions) only in that the returned document will not necessarily be a DefaultSequenceDocument
        Parameters:
        sourceDocument - The sequence to extract from
        extractionOptions - the options to use when extracting. The same extractionOptions should be reused for calls that perform many extractions on the same sequence as this allows caching of sequence properties and therefore improved performance. Methods like SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions.setIntervals(java.util.List) and SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions.setOverrideName(String) can be used between each call to this method.
        Returns:
        the extracted sequence document, or null if SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions.progressListener was canceled.
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if there is insufficient memory to load the annotations in tracks
        Since:
        API 4.800 (Geneious 8.0.0)

      • extract

        public static SequenceDocument extract(SequenceDocument sourceDocument,
                       SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions extractionOptions)
        Extracts one or more intervals from a sequence as a new sequence document. This differs from extractIntervals(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.sequence.SequenceDocument, com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.implementations.SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions) only in that the returned document will not necessarily be a DefaultSequenceDocument
        Parameters:
        sourceDocument - The sequence to extract from
        extractionOptions - the options to use when extracting. The same extractionOptions should be reused for calls that perform many extractions on the same sequence as this allows caching of sequence properties and therefore improved performance. Methods like SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions.setIntervals(java.util.List) and SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions.setOverrideName(String) can be used between each call to this method.
        Returns:
        the extracted sequence document, or null if SequenceExtractionUtilities.ExtractionOptions.progressListener was canceled.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - whose cause is an XMLSerializationException if there is insufficient memory to load the annotations in tracks
        Since:
        API 4.14 (Geneious 5.1)

      • getExtractionName

        public static String getExtractionName(String extractionType,
                       String annotationName,
                       String sequenceName,
                       boolean appendExtractionType)
        Create a name for an extracted region
        Parameters:
        extractionType - eg. "reverse complement", "translation" or "extraction". Can be others.
        annotationName - the name of the annotation being extracted, or null if not extracting an annotation
        sequenceName - the name of the sequence being extracted from
        appendExtractionType - true if the extraction type string should be appended. eg. this would be false if the entire sequence is being extracted from an alignment
        Returns:
        a name for the resulting extracted sequence (or alignment).
